                                                                                            ($ In Thousands)

c) Program Growth in FY 2027 ............................................................................................................................................................................................. $46,928

           1) Active Duty Military End Strength Growth ............................................................................................................................................... $14,928
           Increases funds to support the active duty military end strength growth. The increased funding will cover the recruit training
           operational costs for Basic Military Training (BMT). BMT is the initial training and entry point into military service for enlisted
           accessions. The lack of resources will reduce the capacity to meet the increased enlisted accession throughput. This increase is the
           first of multi-year investment to support active duty end strength growth.

           OP32:
           308 Travel of Persons
           401 DLA Energy (Fuel Products)
           418 Air Force Retail Supply (General Support Division)
           920 Supplies and Materials (Non-Fund)
           922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract
           955 Other Costs (Medical Care)
           964 Other Cost (Subsistence and Support of Persons)
           989 Other Services

           (FY 2026 Base: $26,664)

           2) Recruit Training - Basic Military Training (BMT) NEXT .......................................................................................................................... $32,000
           Increases funds for Air Education Training Command's (AETC) Basic Military Training competency-based curriculum, expanding on the
           PACER FORGE operational exercise and creating immersive training environments to produce mission-ready Airmen. This investment will
           directly support the Department of War's warrior ethos and warfighter efforts, while positioning Air Force's relative advantage in developing
           the enlisted force. Increased funding will cover training range equipment, immersion center equipment, training support facilities, and
           individual equipment issue.

           OP32:
           418 Air Force Retail Supply (General Support Division)
           925 Equipment Purchases (Non-Fund)

           (FY 2026 Base: $26,664)




