                                                                                   423
                                                                     DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE
                                                                       Fiscal Year (FY) 2027 Budget
                                                                   Operation and Maintenance, Air Force
                                                                  Budget Activity: Training and Recruiting
                                                           Detail by Subactivity Group: Specialized Skill Training
                                                                              ($ In Thousands)

I. Description of Operations Financed:
Provides Department of the Air Force and other service members the initial skills training (Specialty Code awarding) and education essential to managing complex weapon
systems and performing other mission-related tasks. Additionally, this training provides the enhanced technical skills needed throughout a member's career to accomplish
the mission. Programs include requirements for initial, follow-on, and supplemental technical skills training. Initial skills training includes technical courses ranging in length
from five to 50+ weeks. This training covers a broad spectrum of courses from intelligence, foreign language training initiatives, Defense English Language Program
initiatives (for which Secretary of the Air Force (SECAF) is the Executive Agent), health care, and financial management, to precision measurement equipment repair,
ultimately funding the training pipeline and mitigating unit-level under-manning. In addition, funding supports the development of Career Development Courses (CDCs) and
end-of-course exams for Active Duty, Guard, and Reserve personnel, and sometimes includes Sister Services, Civil Air Patrol (CAP), Civilians, and Government
Contractor Personnel.


II. Force Structure Summary:
This program funds eight specialized skills training centers, including subordinate detachments and operating locations at Goodfellow Air Force Base (AFB), Texas;
Keesler AFB, Mississippi; Joint Base San-Antonio-Lackland (JBSA-Lackland), Texas; Maxwell AFB, Alabama; Vandenberg AFB, California; Wright Patterson AFB, Ohio;
Defense Foreign Language Center, Monterey, California; and Sheppard AFB, Texas. For functional development, Survival, Evasion, Resistance and Escape (SERE)
training is also accomplished at Fairchild AFB, Washington; and Eielson AFB, Alaska. Air Force Career Development Academy (AFCDA), headquartered at Keesler AFB,
Mississippi with seven operational locations across four states, is the named Air Force authority and agency responsible to develop, deliver, and manage all Total Force
career development courses (CDCs) and specialized courses in support of the total force upgrade training program.




                                                                                                                                         $$, $$54cfeb5d8468e630049506b038b7ea045db20efa1aa09209a60f9006910bd107$$, $$O&M/FY27/Air Force/FY27 Air Force Operation & Maintenance Volume I.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:15.70986+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
