                                                                             ($ In Thousands)

4) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $4,224
Increased funding and manpower (44 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Airlift Operations Program established requirements.
The FY2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to provide the initial skills training and education essential to managing
complex weapons systems. Additionally. this program provides the enhanced technical skills needed throughout a member's career
to accomplish the Air Force's mission.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $195,280; FTE Base: 1,804; 44 FTE)

5) General Skills Training - Cyber Training ................................................................................................................................................... $9,399
Increase will align training to the DoW Cyberspace Workforce Framework in accordance DOW Directive (DoWD) 8140.01, Cyber
Workforce Management, ultimately delivering foundational cyber training to approximately 4,700 total force personnel annually.
Increase supports cyber training range infrastructure, instructors, and advanced training internships with the National Security
Agency.

OP32:
920 Supplies and Materials (Non-Fund)

(FY 2026 Base: $279,033)




