INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_AIRFOR_X_397$$, 2027, $$Air Force$$, $$OM_AIRFOR$$, NULL, NULL, $$DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, Subactivity Group 32A
                                                         439
                                                                      DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE
                                                                          Fiscal Year (FY) 2027 Budget
                                                                    Operation and Maintenance, Air Force
                                                                   Budget Activity: Training and Recruiting
                                                                  Detail by Subactivity Group: Flight Training
                                                                                ($ In Thousands)

I. Description of Operations Financed:
Flying training programs include Academy Glider and Powered Flight Programs, Introductory Flight Training (IFT), Undergraduate Pilot Training (UPT) (including Euro
North Atlantic Treaty Organization Joint Jet Pilot Training (ENJJPT)), Combat System Officer (CSO) Training, Air Battle Manager (ABM) Training, Undergraduate Remotely
Piloted Aircraft Training (URT), Introduction to Fighter Fundamentals (IFF), and Pilot Instructor Training (PIT). UPT is taught at three Air Education and Training Command
(AETC) bases and one Army Base: Vance Air Force Base (AFB), Oklahoma; Columbus AFB, Mississippi; Laughlin AFB, Texas; and Fort Novosel, Alabama. ENJJPT
produces pilots for the United States and participating NATO countries and is taught at Sheppard AFB, Texas. Three bases conduct IFF training for fighter-bound pilot
training graduates: Joint Base San Antonio-Randolph (JBSA-Randolph), Texas; Columbus AFB, Mississippi; and Sheppard AFB, Texas. JBSA-Randolph's program also
includes all PIT training where Instructor Pilots receive extensive training in their assigned aircraft (T-6, T-1, or T-38). Additionally, pilot training is provided to international
students through the Aviation Leadership Program (ALP). CSO training is conducted at Naval Air Station (NAS) Pensacola, Florida; ABM Training at Tyndall AFB, Florida;
and RPA training at JBSA-Randolph, Texas.


II. Force Structure Summary:
This Subactivity Group supports 11 aircraft types at eight flying training wings and operating bases. Aircraft types: T-1, T-6, T-38, TH-1H, TG-10, TG-15, TG-16, UV-18, T-
41, T-51 and T-53. Operating bases: JBSA-Randolph, Texas; Vance AFB, Oklahoma; Columbus AFB, Mississippi; Laughlin AFB, Texas; Sheppard AFB, Texas; Ft
Novosel, Alabama (redesignated from Fort Rucker, Alabama); USAF Academy, Colorado; and NAS Pensacola, Florida.




