1) Advanced Flight Training - Advanced Pilot Trainer ................................................................................................................................ $73,060
The Enhancing High-End Training and Readiness Effort is focused on improving the lethality and preparedness of the force through
realistic, large-scale, and technologically advanced training. Increased funds primarily support the operational beddown requirements
for the T-7 aircraft. The increased funding will cover operational site improvements, maintenance and support equipment, and
furnishing in existing facilities. This investment aligns with the National Defense Strategy to Supercharge the U.S. Defense Industrial
Base by ensuring the Air Force can effectively field and sustain the T-7 aircraft.

OP32:
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract
957 Other Costs (Lands and Structures)

(FY 2026 Base: $167,083)

2) Civilian Pay - Average Workyear Cost Adjustment................................................................................................................................. $10,476
Increase in civilian personnel compensation adjusts average workyear costs. Each year, The Air Force uses detailed execution and
cost factor analysis to update civilian compensation costs for the purpose of accurately forecasting budget estimates for the civilian
workforce. The Subactivity Group average cost adjustment is a result of these changes as well as updated pay raise, awards and
benefit assumptions.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $274,387; FTE Base: 2,124)

3) Civilian Pay - Enhanced Performance Award Pool for DoW Civilian Employees ..................................................................................... $3,747
Increased funding strengthens the Department's ability to recognize and reward the civilian workforce whose expertise and continuity
underpin mission success. Expanded award capacity helps retain the talent that sustains warfighter readiness, drives innovation, and
ensures uninterrupted support across the enterprise. Investing in civilian recognition directly reinforces the workforce that delivers
stability, operation excellence, and long-term capability for the Department.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $274,387; FTE Base: 2,124)




