                     3) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization ....................................................................................................................................................... $316
                     Increase funding and manpower (2 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
                     Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
                     March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
                     efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Professional Development Education Program
                     established requirements. The FY2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support and enhance all aspects of Air
                     Force Operations. Developmental Education teach Airmen to plan, prepare, and react to the unknown, and to find innovative
                     solutions to problems within a highly technical and dynamic battlespace.

                     OP32:
                     101 Executive General Schedule

                     (FY 2026 Base: $110,794; FTE Base: 775; 2 FTE)


