                                                                           ($ In Thousands)


Professional Military Education:
FY 2025 Actuals reflect enrollment data sourced from Air University's Student Lifecycle Management System and reconciled with component schoolhouses.
FY 2026-FY 2027 Enacted and Requested are based HAF/A1D FY 2026 - 2030 Officer/Enlisted PME Program Requirements Document (PRD) dated October 10, 2025;
DL is straight-line from FY 2025 Actuals due to absence of a PRD.

Professional Continuing Education:
FY 2025 Actuals reflect enrollment data source from Air University's Student Lifecycle Management System and reconciled with component schoolhouses.
FY 2026-2027 Enacted and Requested are primarily projected from the FY 2025 Actuals and aligned with targeted requirements from the Cyberspace and Nuclear PCE
PRDs.

Graduate Education:
FY 2025 Actuals reflect verified enrollment figures reported directly by the respective degree-granting institutions: AFIT/EN, AFIT/CI, and SAASS.
FY 2026-2027 Enacted and Requested are held constant with the FY 2025 Actuals reported by AFIT/EN, AFIT/CI, and SAASS.

- PME includes in-resident AWC, ACSC, SOS, SNCOA, Chief Leadership Course (CLC), Enlisted Professional Military Education (EMPE) Instructor, all CONUS NCOAS;
PME distance learning includes AWC, ACSC, SOS, OLMP, SNCOA, NCOA, and ALS. Numbers includes IAAFA for SOS and NCOA CONUS (AD).
- Air Force includes all active duty Air Force and Air Force civilians.
- Other includes other Sister Services, non-US, other federal agencies, and other non-federal agencies.
- Professional Continuing Education includes resident, satellite, and distance learning offerings for AETC-sponsored courses only, to include, both AETC funded and user-
funded students in those courses.
- Graduate Education includes all students attending regular and special programs (including SAASS, IDE to AFIT/NPS). Does not include AFIT part-time, certificates or
Medical Graduate Education, and does not include School of Advanced Military Studies (SAMS), School of Advanced Warfighting (SAW), Joint Advanced Warfighting
School (JAWS) that are part of the Air Force Education Requirements Board (AFERB) Man-years but not AU.
- Workload is based on 246 training day.




