INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_AIRFOR_X_426$$, 2027, $$Air Force$$, $$OM_AIRFOR$$, NULL, NULL, $$DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, Subactivity Group 32C
                                                                                    468
                                                                   DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE
                                                                       Fiscal Year (FY) 2027 Budget
                                                                 Operation and Maintenance, Air Force
                                                                Budget Activity: Training and Recruiting
                                                              Detail by Subactivity Group: Training Support
                                                                             ($ In Thousands)

I. Description of Operations Financed:
Funds Enterprise-wide efforts to provide comprehensive education, training, support services, empowering Airmen and Guardians to develop essential competencies. It
establishes a coherent delivery system and modernizes training to ensure capabilities align with modern life cycle content. This enables the execution of mission-type
orders to outpace our adversaries. General education and training support programs offer core learning services such as student and faculty management, course
development and delivery, and the use of reporting, testing, and collaborative tools. These programs also focus on data transformation and automated training processes,
including scheduling, tracking, certifications, and resource optimization. The training development and requirements capability delivers modernized training designed to
equip Airmen and Guardians with experiential learning in foundational and occupational competencies. Using advanced analytics, it transforms technical training to provide
ready, relevant, and immersive experiences. This is achieved through a learning ecosystem that leverages artificial intelligence including augmented reality, virtual reality,
mixed reality, extended reality (AR/VR/MR/XR), and other machine learning to tailor training.

Supports essential training functions encompassing Management Headquarters Training, Advanced Distance Learning, and Training and Support to units. Headquarters
Air Education and Training Command provides positive command, control, and guidance to the Air Force Training Establishment. Field Training Detachments (FTDs)
conduct on-site training at active, guard and reserve installations on weapon systems identified to specific commands.


II. Force Structure Summary
Headquarters Air Education and Training Command (AETC) at Randolph AFB provides oversight and management of multiple enterprise level learning management and
training systems, with internal key analysis services provided by AETC/A9 and AETC's Studies and Analysis Squadron (SAS). The Air Force has 45 Field Training
Detachments, including various worldwide locations. The goal of all is to support modern learning methodologies and ensure that Airmen have seamless access to
educational resources anytime and anywhere, thus fostering a more effective and immersive training environment.




                                                                                                                                     $$, $$3f78068d32b717e16e1b887068273c1999323fc46ea8d2b466ca5f2e4d6d6e6d$$, $$O&M/FY27/Air Force/FY27 Air Force Operation & Maintenance Volume I.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:15.70986+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
