                                                   Detail by Subactivity Group: Off Duty and Voluntary Education
                                                                          ($ In Thousands)

I. Description of Operations Financed
The Voluntary Education Program is a recruiting, retention, and readiness tool which provides active duty personnel opportunities for professional and personal
development through military tuition assistance for industry recognized credentials and post-secondary education programs.

Specific off-duty programs include the Military Tuition Assistance program and AF Credentialing On-Line Opportunities (AFCOOL) programs, as well as civilian pay,
supplies, contracts, training, and infrastructure. The Air Force is directed by Title 10, Sections 2006a and 2007 to provide military tuition assistance.


II. Force Structure Summary
Funding supports Education and Training Sections throughout the Department of the Air Force.




