                     2) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................. $22,862
                     Increased funding and manpower (295 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
                     Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
                     March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
                     efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Logistics Operations Program established
                     requirements, resulting in a suppressed baseline, which produces a larger year-over-year variance. The FY 2027 request reflects the
                     full requirement necessary to support essential logistical support services like Repair Network Integration, Engine Water Wash (to
                     improve operating efficiency) and Tri-Service Joint Oil Analysis, which detects aircraft engine failure.

