                     Increase funds the Air Force's expanding large-scale exercise portfolio. Transport services enables the strategic prepositioning and
                     redistribution of equipment essential for major exercises such as Mobility Guardian, Resolute Force Pacific (REFORPAC), Freedom
                     Shield, and others throughout the Pacific, European, and Arctic theatres which validate agile combat employment concepts, multi-
                     domain operations, and coalition interoperability under the new Air Expeditionary Wing (AEW) 2.0 construct. The program is a direct
                     enabler of exercise equipment staging, including vehicles, munitions handling equipment, communications systems, and support
                     assets ensuring forces arrive ready to execute complex training scenarios. This increase addresses the growing demand for
                     equipment prepositioning ahead of expanded exercise schedules, which are critical to force readiness, operational concept validation,
