         c) Program Growth in FY 2027 ............................................................................................................................................................................................... $9,222

                     1) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $1,615
                     Increased funding and manpower (17 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
                     Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
                     March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
                     efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Technical Support Activities Program established
                     requirements. The FY2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support activities fund Acquisition and Command
                     support for Headquarters Air Force; Air Force Life Cycle Management Center (AFLCMC); and Air Force Operational Test and
                     Evaluation Center (AFOTEC).

