2) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................. $11,504
Increase funding and manpower (83 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Administration Program established requirements.
The FY2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support Enterprise-Wide programs like Substance Abuse Control
program, Mortuary Affairs and Air Force Warrior and Survivor Care, along with funding for Office of the Secretary of the Air Force and
Air Staff operations.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $715,632; FTE Base: 3,689; 83 FTE)

3) Servicewide Administration - Alignment of Military Services Integrated Personnel and Pay System .................................................... $58,400
Funding supports OMB and OPM led effort, “Federal Human Resource (HR) 2.0” to consolidate and modernize federal HR systems
and will accelerate activities necessary to meet Defense Finance and Accounting Service (DFAS) enterprise data exchange and
data-quality requirements. Without this investment, reliance on Service-specific pay modules creates costly duplication and delays
the transition to a single, modernized platform, ultimately compromising pay accuracy, auditability, and timeliness for our Airmen and
Guardians. Additionally, these activities directly enable the Department to achieve full auditability.

OP32:
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract

(FY 2026 Base: $220,040)




