INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_NAVY_X_473$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$OM_NAVY$$, NULL, NULL, $$Department of the Navy$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, 3B4K
                                                                                                                                            (Page 16 of 16)
                                                                            Department of the Navy
                                                                     FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                       Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                                     Budget Activity: Training and Recruiting
                                                           Activity Group: Recruiting & Other Training And Education
                                                            Detail by Subactivity Group: Recruiting and Advertising
I. Description of Operations Financed:

The Recruiting Support Program provides for the operation and maintenance costs of recruiting men and women for enlisted, officer candidate and officer status positions in the
Active and Reserve components of the Navy.

    -    The Naval Sea Cadet Corps (NSCC) is a congressionally mandated program (chartered by Congress in 1962 - Public Law 87-655) for young men and women ages 13-17
         who are interested in developing their skills in leadership, basic seamanship, courage, self-reliance, and military discipline. The program also improves the Cadet's
         knowledge of Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math (STEM), and prepares them for military service or selection to the Naval Academy. These efforts are
         accomplished through comprehensive summer and winter training programs where cadets are taught basic military, naval, and aviation skills. Funds are used to support
         the logistics of these training efforts and to defray volunteers' and cadets' expenses to provide increased access to students seeking to participate.

    -    Naval Special Warfare Command (NSWC) Navy Parachute Team (NPT) (Leap Frogs) performs parachute demonstrations at Navy Recruiting Command (NRC), NSWC
         and Navy Office of Community Outreach (NAVCO) sponsored events. Beginning in FY11 NRC absorbed the responsibility to fund the team's cost of travel, lodging, and
         aircraft (when necessary) for NPT.

The Department's Advertising Program in support of recruiting efforts is comprised of a national advertising campaign that is complemented by local advertising and public service
announcements. To increase awareness and consideration of Navy career opportunities and generate quality leads from the target audience (youth 17-24), the department
historically relies on a media mix that includes national broadcast and cable TV, radio, print advertising in magazines, direct response programs, recruiting booklets/pamphlets,
Internet banner advertising, Internet web sites, and social media. Included in the overall advertising program are marketing programs targeted at diversity market segments with
the primary objective of increasing the number of quality diversity officer accessions. In addition to the general program areas supported by national advertising, the Navy supports
the high priority nuclear officer, aviation officer, enlisted prior service, medical officer, and diversity programs through digital marketing, magazine advertising, direct response
programs, point-of-sale materials, and field advertising.

The Information Technology (IT) Program manages the Automated Data Processing (ADP) and office information technology to support the recruiting functions at the Navy
Recruiting Command and the Navy Talent Acquisition Group (NTAG) field operations. IT enables the ability to coordinate and direct all automated data processing, planning, and
development efforts with other commands, military services, and civilian contractors. IT provides telecommunications support for Navy Recruiting through voice and data
communications, electronic mail, Local Area Networks (LANs), Metropolitan Area Networks (MANs), and Wide Area Networks (WANs) and provides training for IT users.
Information Technology is crucial because of its ability to evaluate and select systems and software, as well as formulate and disseminate information technology policy standards.


II. Force Structure Summary:

Program provides support for 1,476 recruiting facilities with 5,100 authorized production recruiters (FY27) and approximately 1,973 support billets (includes SELRES) and 219
contractors located in all 50 states and in Guam, Puerto Rico, Virgin Islands (St. Thomas), Japan, Italy, and Germany.




