3) B-1 Aircraft Operations - Training ................................................................................................................................................................ $251
Increase in funding is required to support aircrew training for aircraft conversions, B-1 to B-21. This funding is essential to
establishing a stable training pipeline, ensuring that student production requirements are met, and enabling the Air Force Reserve to
field its next generation bomber fleet in a timely manner to maintain readiness and meet the needs of the Joint Force.

 OP-32 308 Travel
(FY 2026 Base: $11,643)

4) Communications .......................................................................................................................................................................................... $194
Increase to fund secure voice communications, wireless, conferencing services etc. Provides for updated long haul communication
circuits; supports messaging services and tools for communication and information sharing.

OP-32 671 Infrastructure services
OP-32 914 Purchased communications

5) Enhanced Performance Award Pool for DoW Civilians ......................................................................................................................... $11,595
The increase strengthens the Department’s ability to recognize and reward the civilian workforce whose expertise and continuity
underpin mission success. Expanded award capacity helps retain the talent that sustains warfighter readiness, drives innovation, and
ensures uninterrupted support across the enterprise. Investing in civilian recognition directly reinforces the workforce that delivers
stability, operational excellence, and long-term capability for the Department.


OP-31 101,103 Civilian Personnel Compensation
(FY 2026 Base: $724,744)

6) Flying Hour Executability ...................................................................................................................................................................... $166,123
A critical investment of additional hours is requested to address immediate readiness shortfalls, meet Combatant Command
demands, and ensure effective integration with the Joint Force. These essential hours allow aircrews to practice and validate complex
tactics in high-fidelity training, including large-scale joint simulation exercises. Simultaneously, the funding increase stabilizes the
defense industrial supply chain by providing a consistent demand signal for spares and consumables. The combination of enhanced
training and industrial responsiveness underpins the Air Force's ability to sustain high-tempo operations and surge to meet wartime




