                     support UTA participation and sustain uninterrupted training, enabling the force to remain responsive and capable in an evolving
                     threat environment.

                     OP-32, 964 Subsistence and support
                     (FY 2026 Base: $5,429)

                     7) Information Technology Equipment .......................................................................................................................................................... $3,392
                     Increase provides additional funding for information technology (IT) requirements including hardware and software. Additional funding
                     supports the replacement of aging hardware, expansion of inventory to support force structure changes, the beddown of new units,
                     and the onboarding of additional support personnel as well as software updates and the purchase of additional licenses and technical
                     support. IT increases are driven by overall growth to the mission support portfolio, which is required to support growth to the
                     operational portfolio driven by mission changes and increased Joint Force demands.



                     OP-32 925 Equipment
                     (FY 2026 Base: $11,831)

                     8) Medical Care Support ............................................................................................................................................................................... $2,236
                     Funding is provided to support the Optimizing Human Weapons System (OHWS) Initiative, designed to enhance human performance
                     and reduce injury rates across Combat Air Forces squadrons. OHWS embeds strength and conditioning specialists, physical
                     therapists, and related support services directly within operational units to decrease the frequency and severity of neck, back and
                     musculoskeletal injuries. Additionally, increased enables Air Force Reserve to centralize critical medical support functions under the
                     Headquarters Surgeon General Office, improving oversight, standardization and delivery of human-performance services across the
                     enterprise. Increase strengthens the Reserve’s ability to maintain a medically ready force, reduce lost duty time, and enhance long-
                     term aircrew and maintain readiness in support of operational requirements.

                     OP-32 418 Supplies
                     OP-32 955 Medical Care
                     (FY 2026 Base: $2,176)

