           1) Utilities ....................................................................................................................................................................................................... $1,398
           Funding increase for utilities to drive by estimated increased requirement in utility usage as well as funding required to support
           infrastructure upgrades driving increases in electrical transportation costs.

           OP-32 Purchased utilities
           (FY 2026 Base: $26,216)

           2) Supplies and Materials .............................................................................................................................................................................. $1,844
           This increases funds, supplies and materials for base operations and programs. Additional funding is needed to support increased
           requirements for the Integrated Prevention Program, which provides violence prevention services to Air Force Reserve members,
           their families, and the community.

           OP-32 920 Supplies and Materials
           (FY 2026 Base: $10,079)

           3) Reserve Full time Equivalents - Base Support ...................................................................................................................................... $11,524
           Increase in Full-Time Equivalents to support Primary Combat Forces manpower requirements. FY 2027 estimate includes increase to
           support necessary civilian end strength levels. Funding is essential for the efficient execution of critical Air Force Reserve missions in
           support of the Department's priorities and increased readiness demands. Functions supported include safety, law enforcement,
           Sexual Assault Prevention & Response, communications, airfield operations and support, force management and transportation
           support.
           (FY 2026 Base: $360,437; 86 FTE)

           4) Information Technology Support ............................................................................................................................................................... $4,717
           This increase provides funding for information technology support equipment across the Air Force Reserve. Additional resources are
           required to enhance the stability and security of the Air Force Reserve Information Technology enterprise. Funding supports end user
           hardware and software services and tools, enterprise software applications, and the sustainment necessary for service, maintenance,
           and software upgrades. The increase also provides funding for Public Affairs Adobe Creative Cloud licenses required to support UTC
           mission requirements. These licenses enable personnel to securely create, manage, and distribute official documents and digital
           products essential to mission execution.




