                                                           Detail by Subactivity Group: Administration
                                                                          ($ In Thousands)

1) Civilian Pay - Civilian Manpower Realignment ........................................................................................................................................ $-8,480
Decrease transfers funding and manpower from Administration (Subactivity Group 42A, -$8,480, -40 FTEs) and Special Programs
(Subactivity Group 13F, -$2,120, -10 FTEs) to U.S. Air Force, to fund organic civilian professional manpower previously provided by
advisory and assistance service contract support. This action effectively aligns Department of Air Force resources directly supporting
the Secretary of the Air Force.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $73,580; FTE Base: 346; -40 FTE)

2) Civilian Pay - Command and Control Manpower ..................................................................................................................................... $-4,978
Decrease transfers funding and manpower from Administration (Subactivity Group 42A, -$4,978, -27 FTEs), Global C3I & Early
Warning (Subactivity Group 12A -$1,759, -17 FTEs), Education & Training (Subactivity Group 13E, -$9,320, -52 FTEs), Special
Programs (Subactivity Group 13F, -$10,919, -54 FTEs) and Logistics Operations (Subactivity Group 41A, -$470, -5 FTEs) to Space
Operations (Subactivity Group 13C, $21,457, 103 FTEs) and Cyberspace Activities (Subactivity Group 13D, $8,261, 45 FTEs) to
realign resources to support the mission requirements for the standup of Space Forces - Space as a Component Field Command.
Manpower will support command and control of combat operations, strategic planning, ISR, and SATCOM integrated operations. The
transfer enables achievement of theater and global objectives.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $73,580; FTE Base: 346; -27 FTE)




