                                                                         ($ In Thousands)

2) Chief of Space Operations - Targeting Weaponeering Course .............................................................................................................. $12,430
Increase funds the study and course stand-up of a U.S. Space Force Weaponeering course. The training matures the U.S. Space
Force's targeting processes to produce a unified methodology for technical training and skillsets for integration of space weapon
systems into the joint targeting processes. This course coordinates planning efforts with Combatant Commands and Component
Field Commands. This increase improves student throughput by funding training course standup, system integration, training
classroom facilities, associated equipment and software licenses.

OP32:
308 Travel of Persons

(FY 2026 Base: $62,630)

3) Civilian Pay - Average Workyear Cost Adjustment................................................................................................................................... $4,367
Increase in Civilian Personnel compensation adjusts average workyear costs. Each year U.S. Space Force uses detailed execution
and cost factor analysis to update civilian compensation costs for the purpose of accurately forecasting budget estimates for the
civilian workforce. The Subactivity Group average cost adjustment is a result of these changes as well as updated pay raise, awards
and benefit assumptions.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $73,580; FTE Base: 346)

4) Civilian Pay - Enhanced Performance Award Pool for DoW Civilian Employees ........................................................................................ $386
Increased funding strengthens the Department's ability to recognize and reward the civilian workforce whose expertise and continuity
underpin mission success. Expanded award capacity helps retain the talent that sustains warfighter readiness, drives innovation, and
ensures uninterrupted support across the enterprise. Investing in civilian recognition directly reinforces the workforce that delivers
stability, operation excellence, and long-term capability for the Department.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $73,580; FTE Base: 346)




