      iii)Pacific Deterrence Initiative. Increase supports operational and training requirements within the INDOPACOM AOR,                   105,250
         ensuring forward-deployed forces remain ready, capable, and able to respond quickly to regional contingencies and maintain
         deterrence, to support increased Marine Force Structure. (Baseline: $413,836)
      iv)Pacific Deterrence Initiative. Increase supports the expanded scope and scale of units and equipment for Marine Corps               104,617
         ground forces across a Range of Military Operations (ROMO) within the INDOPACOM Area of Responsibility (AOR).
         Additionally, increase supports critical joint exercises, training events, and Operations, Activities, and Investments (OAIs)
         that are essential for campaigning and building a resilient Joint Force. (Baseline: $413,836)
      v)Other Combat Support. Ballistic Protection Systems (BPS): Increase supports the fielding of 80,651 Integrated Helmet                  95,750
         Systems to provide enhanced ballistic protection while integrating hearing, communication, and night vision capabilities for
         improved warfighter effectiveness. (Baseline: $89,659)
      vi)Logistics Combat Element. Intermediate & Organizational Maintenance increase supports Field Level Maintenance of                     84,550
         Amphibious Combat Vehicle (ACV), Ground/ Air Task Oriented Radar (G/ATOR), Navy-Marine Expeditionary Ship
         Interdiction System (NMESIS) and other equipment in support of Marine Expeditionary Forces'. (Baseline: $420,090)
      vii)Aviation Combat Element. Marine Aviation Wing (MAW) increase supports Marine Aviation ground maintenance,                           67,525
         contracted logistics support (CLS), and essential transportation for 1st, 2nd, and 3rd MAW. Additionally, increase ensures the
         MAGTF can provide decisive air superiority to meet any Geographic Combatant Commander's demand, while also providing
         aviation capabilities to support efforts for border security and territorial integrity, as directed by Executive Order 14167,
         "Clarifying the Military's Role in Protecting the Territorial Integrity of the United States" (Baseline: $68,479)
      viii)Ground Combat Element. Increase supports 1st and 2nd Marine Divisions efforts for border security and territorial                  67,031
         integrity, as directed by Executive Order 14167, "Clarifying the Military's Role in Protecting the Territorial Integrity of the
         United States". Additionally, increase supports travel, transportation, and supplies for essential off-station training, directly
         enhancing large-scale CONUS and OCONUS exercises. (Baseline: $707,345)
      ix)Logistics Combat Element. Secondary Repairables increase supports the ability to conduct Depot and Field Level                       64,728
         maintenance performed by the Reparable Issue Point (RIP) that support Amphibious Combat Vehicle (ACV), Ground/ Air
         Task Oriented Radar (G/ATOR), Navy-Marine Expeditionary Ship Interdiction System (NMESIS), and other equipment for
         the Marine Expeditionary Forces. (Baseline: $420,090)
      x)Logistics Combat Element. Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) capability supports Unmanned Aircraft System (UAS)                          58,994
         integration for key pre-deployment exercises, including Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC), Pre-Mission Intelligence Training
         (PMINT), Amphibious Ready Group - Marine Expeditionary Unit Exercise (ARG-MEU EX), and Composite Unit Training
         Exercise (COMPTUEX), to enhance training realism and warfighter readiness for the modern battlefield. (Baseline:
         $420,090)
      xi)Ground Combat Element. Other Combat Support increase reflects the Operations, Activities, and Investments (OAIs) to                  51,991
         support the Marine Corps, including the fielding and integration of unmanned systems and long-range precision fires,
         developing a modernized, combat-credible force prepared to meet enhanced Global Force Management (GFM) demands for
         all Geographic Combatant Commanders (GCCs), Marine force capacity and presence. (Baseline: $707,345)
