      xii)Ground Combat Element. Other Combat Support increase supports Marine Littoral Regiments (MLRs) readiness levels                  51,305
         specified by the Directed Readiness Table (DRT), ensuring forces are postured to meet emerging regional threats, and are
         aligned with Force Design and Stand-in Force (SiF) requirements directly supporting Global Force Management (GFM)
         demands by enabling the purchase of necessary commercial off-the-shelf (COTS) equipment such as ruggedized laptops and
         tablets, portable satellite communications terminals, unmanned aerial systems, and all-terrain vehicles, as well as the
         transportation of gear to the regiments. (Baseline: $707,345)
      xiii)Logistics Combat Element. Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) capability enables the full operational lifecycle throughout          42,178
         assembly, training, deployment, and reset of forward-deployed forces in Japan, ensuring continuous global readiness to
         respond to emerging regional threats, including those posed by China, in alignment with Force Design and Stand-in Force
         (SiF) objectives providing essential logistics such as prepositioned equipment, transport vehicles, and supply chain support
         for rapid response to crises, humanitarian missions, and combat operations. (Baseline: $420,090)
      xiv)Logistics Combat Element. Marine Logistics Group (MLG) increase supports 1st and 2nd MLGs efforts for border security            36,704
         and territorial integrity, as directed by Executive Order 14167, "Clarifying the Military's Role in Protecting the Territorial
         Integrity of the United States" through modernization and streamlining supply and logistics capabilities, recapitalization of
         legacy systems, and Transportation of Things (ToT), Transportation of People (ToP). (Baseline: $420,090)
      xv)Pacific Deterrence Initiative. Increase strengthens combat readiness and equipment capabilities across all Marine Air-            31,039
         Ground Task Force (MAGTF) elements, enabling forward-deployed forces to deter strategic competitors, maintain freedom
         of navigation, and objectives in the Indo-Pacific. (Baseline: $413,836)
      xvi)Other Combat Support. Information Management (IM) increase supports the National Defense Strategy's imperatives of               17,658
         integrated deterrence and campaigning through critical initiatives that build a more lethal and resilient force, capable of
         securing the information advantage. Critical initiatives include Controlled Access Program Control Officers (CAPCOs),
         operationalizing data from the Service Data Office (SDO), resourcing the Information Vandegrift Team (IVT), and expanding
         Service Counterintelligence capabilities. (Baseline: $89,659)
      xvii)Other Combat Support. Family of Chemical, Biological, Radiological and Nuclear (CBRN) Systems increase supports the             17,227
         replacement and resupply of 20,413 Joint Service Lightweight Integrated Suit Technology (JLIST) suits. This investment is
         essential to bolster the credibility of our Integrated Deterrence posture, ensuring the force is protected and capable of
         operating in a CBRN-contaminated environment to deter and, if necessary, defeat aggression from any adversary. (Baseline:
         $89,659)
      xviii)Other Combat Support. Increase supports the fielding of 27,546 Plate Carrier Generation III systems to enhance Marine          15,739
         survivability with life-saving technology, advancing force modernization and ensuring warfighter readiness for the modern
         battlefield (Baseline: $89,659)
      xix)Civilian Personnel. Increases civilian personnel full-time equivalents and associated funding to support combat service          11,656
         support requirements aligned with Force Design and contested logistics, enabling warfighting units to train, exercise, and
         employ modern capabilities as part of an enhanced organizational design to rebalance and optimize the civilian workforce.
         (Baseline: $148,676; +62 civilian FTE)
