                                                                       59                                                (Page 4 of 9)
                                                                           Department of the Navy
                                                                   FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                 Operation and Maintenance, Marine Corps
                                                                      Budget Activity: Operating Forces
                                                                    Activity Group: USMC Prepositioning
                                                            Detail by Subactivity Group: Maritime Prepositioning
IV. Performance Criteria and Evaluation Summary:

 Metric Description: Measures the ability to provide Ready For Issue (RFI) equipment and supplies to combatant commanders.
 Metric #1: Attainment Rate = Equipment on-hand / Prepositioning Objective
 Metric #2: Readiness Rate = Equipment on-hand in RFI condition / Equipment on-hand

 Performance Goal: 90% Attainment Rate and 95% Readiness Rate.
 Data Source: U.S. Marine Corps Installations and Logistics; Logistics Plans, Policies, Strategic Mobility Division.

 (# of Units)                                                    FY 2025        FY 2026        FY 2027
 Prepositioning Objective*                                         8,232          8,232          8,232
 Equipment on-hand**                                               7,875          8,067          8,177
 Equipment on-hand in RFI condition                                7,540          7,985          8,042
 Attainment Rate                                                    97%            98%            99%
 Readiness Rate                                                     96%            99%            98%

 FY 2025, FY 2026 and FY 2027 Inventory requirements represent current program objectives and does not include equipment needed to establish future ashore
 prepositioning sites in INDOPACOM. Decisions are pending for the services' equipping strategy and the future ashore site locations and capabilities.

 Current inventory:
 - FY 2026 on-hand quantities represent current equipment status reporting dated January 30, 2026.
 - Attainment and readiness rates improved over the previous year due to updates in strategic assessments, enhanced capabilities, and revised program objectives. Projections
 indicate that increased funding and historical trends will further improve readiness; however, supply chain constraints and lead times will determine the specific timing of
 these gains.
 - FY 2025, FY 2026 and FY 2027 on-hand quantities are projections based on the assumption that attainment will increase ~1% a year. Shortfalls will exist based on new
 equipment fielding priorities.
 - Equipment on-hand in ready for issue condition assumes that funding will remain at an adequate level to maintain a steady readiness rate.

 * FY 2026 Includes Marine Corps major ground readiness reportable equipment and principal end items in accordance with the NAVMC 2907 With Change 4, and FY 2026
 numbers are based on updated NAVMC 2907, which establishes the future approved inventory for the Marine Corps Prepositioning Programs (MCPP). It does not include
 consumable items, reparable items, munitions/ordnance, individual weapons, and aviation support equipment. FY 2025, FY 2026 and FY 2027 are based on current planning
 efforts and is subject to change.

 ** Equipment on-hand excludes excess items to the prepositioning objective.




